.TH "igb_read_mbx_pf" 9 "igb_read_mbx_pf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
igb_read_mbx_pf \- Read a message from the mailbox
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" igb_read_mbx_pf
.BI "(struct e1000_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u32 *msg "  ","
.BI "u16 size "  ","
.BI "u16 vf_number "  ","
.BI "bool unlock "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the HW structure
.IP "msg" 12
The message buffer
.IP "size" 12
Length of buffer
.IP "vf_number" 12
the VF index
.IP "unlock" 12
unlock the mailbox when done?

This function copies a message from the mailbox buffer to the caller's
memory buffer.  The presumption is that the caller knows that there was
a message due to a VF request so no polling for message is needed.
